        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-29T15:14:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we need the full clip generality? I think the idea was that this gets called from GrReducedClip and if we recursively got back into GrReducedClip that\u0027d be bad news. Perhaps we can just assert in GrReducedClip that we don\u0027t make a recursive call?",
      "revId": "36aef22ff568129d9e8d2087a18a138e3161ebfc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "64768dfd_1ab20429",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrRenderTargetContextPriv.h",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 66,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-29T17:14:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The path renderers that use stencilRect() now have regular GrClips. GrReducedClip only calls this function with a GrHardClip or a GrFixedClip. I did add a comment to stencilRect() to assist with any future modifications of GrReducedClip.",
      "parentUuid": "bfffbbb0_d3dad643",
      "revId": "36aef22ff568129d9e8d2087a18a138e3161ebfc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f20f0d35_f50e9a4e",
        "filename": "src/gpu/ops/GrFillRectOp.h",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 43,
      "author": {
        "id": 5230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-29T15:31:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Don\u0027t know if it will show up on perf but, in a lot of cases, we\u0027re passing I() in here but using MakeFromRect.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 43,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 43,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "36aef22ff568129d9e8d2087a18a138e3161ebfc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8b2edbc4_90492afc",
        "filename": "src/gpu/ops/GrFillRectOp.h",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 43,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-29T17:22:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I had initially hoped I could avoid taking a view matrix entirely, but some of the GMs use it. It looks like they only rely on translations so I could update it to take a device-space rect instead, but then the GMs would have to get more complicated to use a local matrix in their FPs.\n\nMakeFromRect can detect I() and then performs no extra math, so I doubt a single matrix type check would show up on perf. Given that, I\u0027ll leave MakeNonAARect with a view matrix for now, unless you feel strongly that the simplification is worth it.",
      "parentUuid": "f20f0d35_f50e9a4e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 43,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 43,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "36aef22ff568129d9e8d2087a18a138e3161ebfc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3d9f021f_037e0657",
        "filename": "src/gpu/ops/GrFillRectOp.h",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 43,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-29T19:22:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Given the subtlety of getting local coords correct with a view matrix I think it makes sense to keep this.",
      "parentUuid": "8b2edbc4_90492afc",
